# 🚗 Full Source Code — Part 1: Data Classes

## 1. User.java — Abstract Base Class
```java
// OOP: ABSTRACTION (abstract class), ENCAPSULATION (private fields)
public abstract class User {
    private String userId;
    private String username;
    private String name;
    private String email;
    private String password;
    private String role;

    public User(String userId, String username, String name, String email, String password, String role) {
        this.userId = userId;
        this.username = username;
        this.name = name;
        this.email = email;
        this.password = password;
        this.role = role;
    }

    // Abstract method - subclasses MUST override this
    public abstract String displayInfo();

    // Getters
    public String getUserId() { return userId; }
    public String getUsername() { return username; }
    public String getName() { return name; }
    public String getEmail() { return email; }
    public String getPassword() { return password; }
    public String getRole() { return role; }

    // Setters
    public void setUsername(String username) { this.username = username; }
    public void setName(String name) { this.name = name; }
    public void setEmail(String email) { this.email = email; }
    public void setPassword(String password) { this.password = password; }
}
```

---

## 2. Admin.java — Inherits from User
```java
// OOP: INHERITANCE (extends User), POLYMORPHISM (overrides displayInfo), METHOD OVERRIDING
public class Admin extends User {

    public Admin(String userId, String username, String name, String email, String password) {
        super(userId, username, name, email, password, "Admin"); // calls parent constructor
    }

    @Override
    public String displayInfo() {
        return "Admin: " + getName() + " (ID: " + getUserId() + ") | Email: " + getEmail();
    }

    public void addCar(Car car) {
        DataStore.cars.add(car);
    }

    public void removeCar(String carId) {
        for (int i = 0; i < DataStore.cars.size(); i++) {
            if (DataStore.cars.get(i).getCarId().equals(carId)) {
                DataStore.cars.remove(i);
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

