## 3. Customer.java — Inherits from User
```java
import java.util.ArrayList;

// OOP: INHERITANCE, POLYMORPHISM (different displayInfo than Admin), ENCAPSULATION
public class Customer extends User {
    private ArrayList<Rental> rentalHistory;

    public Customer(String userId, String username, String name, String email, String password) {
        super(userId, username, name, email, password, "Customer");
        this.rentalHistory = new ArrayList<>();
    }

    @Override
    public String displayInfo() {
        return "Customer: " + getName() + " (ID: " + getUserId() + ") | Rentals: " + rentalHistory.size();
    }

    public ArrayList<Rental> getRentalHistory() { return rentalHistory; }

    public void addRental(Rental rental) { rentalHistory.add(rental); }
}
```

